        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 16 at 4:49PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 449 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Montrose, or near Birch Run, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Saginaw, Frankenmuth, Clio, Birch Run, Montrose, Bridgeport, Burt,
Fosters, Gera, Layton Corners, and Buena Vista Township.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
